  section#whatIsFolding.panel.contentPanel
    a#whatIsFoldingRef.jumpTo
    #whatIsFoldingText
      div
        div
          h4 what is protein folding?
          h2
            | Proteins are functional collections of molecules. To do their
            | work, they assemble themselves into a specific shape, or &lsquo;fold&rsquo;.
        p
          | Proteins are tiny chains of amino acids that perform every
          | function in the body. The problem being; we don&rsquo;t know why they
          | fold in specific ways, making it nearly impossible to tell how a
          | specific protein does its job.
      div
        h4 why does folding matter?
        h2
          | Terminal diseases, like Alzheimer&rsquo;s, Cancer, and Cystic Fibrosis
          | are believed to be caused by protein misfolds.
        p
          | When we discover how, and why proteins fold into specific
          | structures, we can understand what makes things go wrong. Helping
          | us develop therapies for previously incurable diseases.
        cite
          a(href='https://sitn.hms.harvard.edu/flash/2010/issue65/' target='_blank') Courtesy: Harvard.edu
