        h2
          | To accurately understand how a protein will fold, we must simulate
          | the forces in the human body every millionth of a second.
        p
          | With such extreme time scales, each protein chain having more than
          | 10
          sup 30
          |  different combinations. Supercomputers are needed
          |               to even stand a chance at solving for the correct combination.
